
Ionic Command Line Features
===========================

start -> Starts a new Ionic project
serve -> Starts a local development server
platform -> Configure platform targets
build -> Locally build app for a platform
emulate -> Emulate app in simulator
run -> Run app on device

Install Ionic 
=============
> npm install ionic -g
> npm install cordova -g

Starting a New project
======================
> ionic start firstIonic blank 

Run your app
============
> ionic serve

Run your app on the simulator
=============================
> ionic platform add android
> ionic build android
> ionic emulate android

Note: before you run the emulator make sure you have to install android sdk

Run your app on your device
===========================
> ionic run android

Ionic Starter Templates
=======================

blank

Tabs
> ionic start ionicTabsApp Tabs

Side Menu
> ionic start EliteScheduleApp  sidemenu

